{"_id":"b2d482f4-a0be-36fa-a6d2-4551c1ba40c4","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"28dde5772b48c92e08b8050411aa5ba8","message":"You can't just \"make something async\". If it's asynchronous by nature (e.g., I/O), then use asynchronous APIs. The easiest way to do async/await is to start at the \"leaves\". So saying \"make waitforinput() asynchronous\" is starting at the wrong end; instead, you must make the code represented by \"while(true);\" asynchronous.","postId":"2014_02_synchronous-and-asynchronous-delegate-da774236-3c77-3bd8-9d4d-1e1e1260e7e5","replyTo":"e7d9442e-88bc-384d-80f0-498e856c3c9b","date":"2015-10-30T23:38:10Z","timestamp":1446248290,"authorUserId":"disqus:stephen_cleary"}